title: Border, 1972-42-39-a/d, 1800–25
medium: Block-printed and flocked on handmade paper
description:
Pairs of stylized swans holding between them lyres that rest upon garlands of quatrefoils and lozenges. The garlands terminate at each swan with a trident/scepter. Printed in rust and dark red-brown flocking, yellow, tan, white and shades of gray over a blue base coat.

H# 319A
